						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Vijayagaṇḍagōpāla Year: 3, <hi rend="italic">Ṛishabha</hi>, śu. di. 5. <hi rend="italic">Anusham</hi> = 1253 A.D. Other details are irregular.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription registers a gift of all the land in the (village) Peruṅgārai in Paiyyūr-kōṭṭam as <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya</hi>, exempting it from taxes such as <hi rend="italic">kaḍamai, poṉvari kudiraivari</hi> etc., as <hi rend="italic">maḍappuṟam</hi> to Mudaliyār Śrī Nandikēśvaradēvara <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Āḻiyāvratamkoṇḍa-Mudaliyār and his disciples in Tiruvoṟṟiyūr in Puḻar-kōṭṭam <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vikramachōḷa-vaḷanāḍu (a sub-division) of Jayaṅgoṇḍachōḷa-maṇḍalam, by Nāyaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Kiḍārattaraiyaṉ.</p>						

						</summary>
